the folks in my guild tend to say get level 60 first then work on AA. Their point is that your level helps with the day to day things (spells, resists, pulling, aggro from greens etc.) and the AA skills are purely frosting on the cake. <br>
<br>
If getting level 60 isn't an issue for you though and you are satisfied with the spells for your level, go for a few points into the AA.<br>
