What they said, 51-52<br>
<br>
I had no jboots, so I went to 70% (couldn't stand not getting any normal exp, tried 100 first) until I got run 3, been at 40% ever since until I got to 55, at which point, I was anxious to get some of the archetype abilities, so I went to 60.  <br>
<br>
I don't recommend this for everyone, especially non-soloists.  The only reason I do what I do is that level 60 is not that urgent to me, despite the new spells at 60, and I know I'll be able to get it pretty much whenever I set my mind to it, however, being proud of my character is.  I get alot more pride out of him when I pull off that 1497 crit for all to gawk at than I did when I was just another nuker.  I also have alot more blues available to me now at 55 than I will at 60 that are soloable.  I choose to get the AA skills that I want that aren't necessarily what the guild would like to see out of me now, and I'll worry about pleasing them later.  It is my character afterall.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><img src="http://members.cox.net/aurthur/brusig.jpg"><br><br>
